<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-Wg1uGfgDx5R79K0vEX6E4A" name=",_J3DBEKZFEeCmzNtTCfivQw" guid="-Wg1uGfgDx5R79K0vEX6E4A" changeDate="2011-08-18T10:06:26.667-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The test specification, specifies and selects the simulation scenarios, test cases and test data based upon the methods&#xD;
    selected in the&amp;nbsp;HW-SW integration&amp;nbsp;test plan.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Test cases shall be derived from&amp;nbsp;a combination of the appropriate&amp;nbsp;methods detailed in &quot;Table 3-Methods for&#xD;
    deriving test cases for item integration&quot; located at&amp;nbsp;ISO 26262, volume 4, clause 8.4.1.5. In summary the following&#xD;
    methods can be employed&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of requirements, which is a technique that is highly recommended for items of all ASIL level&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of external and internal interfaces&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of environmental conditions and operational use cases&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of field experience&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    These techniques are recommended for items with an ASIL of A and highly recommended for items with an ASIL of&amp;nbsp; B,C&#xD;
    or D&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The following techniques are recommended for items with an ASIL of A or B and highly recommended for items with an ASIL&#xD;
    of&amp;nbsp; C or D&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Generation and analysis of equivalence classes for hardware software integration.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of boundary values&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Knowledge or experience based upon error guessing&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of functional dependencies&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
        Analysis of common limit conditions, sequences and sources of common cause&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    It is advised that the user refers to ISO 26262 volume 8, clause 9.4.2 for further details on the contents of&#xD;
    the&amp;nbsp;test(verification) specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>If the item is ASIL C or D then a specification for the complete testing of the hardware software interface is required.</keyConsiderations>
  <purpose>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    To specify the test methods and test cases that are used to test the HW and SW that are integrated together.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
